id: pm-surv
title: "GH-529: init --agent-guidance emits run-tests.mjs linked-test example that may not exist in the target repo"
description: "pm init --agent-guidance add writes an auto-managed AGENTS.md quickstart block whose linked-test example is 'pm test <id> --add command=\"node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- ...\"'. That script is pm-cli-repo-specific; in arbitrary host repos the trusted onboarding guidance points at a non-existent command, causing confusion and linked-test-evidence drift. Fix direction: render a repo-agnostic placeholder template ('<your project test command>') or detect an existing test entry point (package.json scripts.test) before rendering a concrete command. Class: environment/capability-aware hint rendering — same family as pm-qljv (package-only reindex hint) and the pm-mpbb 'derive hints from actual capability' ledger; audit other init-guidance hints for repo-specific assumptions at fix time."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,gh-issue,init
created_at: "2026-07-13T08:57:09.402Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T08:57:09.402Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: Generated guidance never names a command absent from the target repo (placeholder template or detected test entry); init-guidance hints audited for repo-specific assumptions; GH-529 closed
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
